label.value: restaurant or fast food preparation process

definition.value: The process of preparing and serving food in a restaurant or fast food outlet.
The process of sourcing and selling food at a street vending establishment.

Street vendor food may be prepared at on- or off-site locations, commissaries (e.g., wrapped fresh sandwiches) or food industry establishments (e.g., bagged potato chips). Examples of street vendors include hot dog stands, truck sandwich vendors, and vendors that sell bagged potato chips.
